data.description: Seller to contribute $5K towards closing costs or rate buy down with full price offer. There is No HOA. Tucked away in the village, surrounded by pines and an aspen grove, within a short walk to town sits this quaint 2 bdrms, 1 bath Mtn Cabin. This property features a Dry She Shed/bunkhouse/Workshop, working 2-seater outhouse, covered wood storage, a small fenced yard, small shed and 2 RV outlets (30 & 50 amp).  Do you long for a weekend getaway?  A year-round retreat from the hustle and bustle? This cabin is peaceful, private, and accessible. Sit on your deck and enjoy the views or gather around the flagstone patio to enjoy the fire pit.  Most near by neighbors are seasonal so it is quite peaceful. There are many wildlife visitors, check the photos to see a few of the visitors you will encounter throughout the year. The 2 heat sources are a propane fireplace and wood stove.  Seller is removing the 2 painted sheds on the property.  The Cabin has a private well and septic vault. It has been a year-round home for many years. Looking for a great investment opportunity?  This is the property! Could potentially be used as a STR. Dry shed has been used for extra living space with a camping toilet.  Buyer would be responsible for verifying and researching process with Larimer County and obtain all the proper licenses. Cabin is being sold As-Is with no warranty. Requires a 48 hour notice to show.
